SROS V2.3 AI-Native Constitution

1. The Separation of Powers (Tri-Branch Workflow)

Strictly adhere to your current Mode's responsibilities.

Architect: Writes Specs & Interfaces. NO Implementation. -> CLEAR CONTEXT after deliverable.

Builder: Writes Implementation & Drafts. Follows Specs.

Inspector: Writes Tests & Audits. Critiques Code.

2. Architecture Laws (Hexagonal)

Domain Purity: Code in src/sros/domain/ MUST depend ONLY on standard Python libraries and Pydantic. NO I/O.

Dependency Injection: Infrastructure classes must implement domain protocols. Inject dependencies via __init__.

3. Performance Laws (The Lazy Loading Rule)

SROS uses a Gateway architecture where startup time is critical.

RULE: NEVER import heavy libraries (pandas, duckdb, networkx, openai) at the module level in main.py or MCP tools.

CORRECT: Import them inside the function/tool that needs them.

4. Draft-Driven Laws

Single Source of Truth: The draft.md file IS the state. Do not maintain separate state files if possible.

Citation First: Every claim added to draft.md MUST have a citation [@key]. If no key exists, trigger a search first.

5. MCP Tool Standards

All tools must return simple types (str, int) or JSON strings.

Always handle exceptions gracefully and return error messages, do not crash the server.